title: Ticket #5612: cannot import python binding class htcondor (segfault)
description:
On Debian 7 and HTCondor 8.5.3, the python htcondor class cannot be imported. 

  [greatdane:wrapper-testing] python -c "import htcondor"
  Segmentation fault

No issue on Debian 8: 

  thomas.downes@condor-test:~$ python -c "import htcondor"
  thomas.downes@condor-test:~$

Although LIGO intends on upgrading to Debian 8, we haven't yet.
remarks:
2016-Apr-08 16:52:11 by tpdownes:
Actually, I cannot replicate this on any other host. It reliably occurs on this particular host. Any command I can run to diagnose?

2016-Apr-08 17:44:33 by gthain:
My first suggestion would be to run

strace -e open python -c 'import htcondor'

and make sure it is finding the right files.
